###Sleeping Pad

I originally splurged and bought a [Therm-a-Rest EvoLite Regular](https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00PZKXB2Y/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=bonktothefi07-20&camp=1789&creative=9325&linkCode=as2&creativeASIN=B00PZKXB2Y&linkId=acea382d7dd633df3e862490fd322989).
It had all the specs: self-inflating, super lightweight, and compact.

But it sucked.
It wasn't as thick or comfortable as expected, and provided little insulation against the ground.
Despite taking extra special care it quickly got a hole and defalted over night.

I decided self-inflating pads were too high maintainence for me and bought this [cheap foldable foam mat](https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B01APD5880/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=bonktothefi07-20&camp=1789&creative=9325&linkCode=as2&creativeASIN=B01APD5880&linkId=31606083f86a1975d371a88494dda17d).
It was more comfortable than the first sleeping pad and extremely durable.
So for now I'm sticking with it.

###Sleeping Bags

Right now I have two extremes:

1. A [sleeping bag liner](https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0026JLUYI/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=bonktothefi07-20&camp=1789&creative=9325&linkCode=as2&creativeASIN=B0026JLUYI&linkId=04a2b567d915fcbc56498139be2b0263) that also works well by itself in the summertime.

2. A [0 degree sleeping bag](https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00G6HTG2E/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=bonktothefi07-20&camp=1789&creative=9325&linkCode=as2&creativeASIN=B00G6HTG2E&linkId=6d70f1606d96ac088f6ea2c6d657044a).
P.S. I get cold easily, so I doubt this would actually keep me warm at 0 degrees.
The bag was also much larger than expected, definitely wouldn't classify this one as compact!


###Pillow

I recently found [this inflatable pillow by FavorGear](https://www.walmart.com/ip/Inflatable-Pillows-Camping-FavorGear-Compact-Travel-Pillow-Ultralight-Comfortable-Backpacking-Hiking-Airplane-Train-Car-Office/572841940).
The brand is new to me but it works great.
The pillow is comfortable andextremely compact: with the push of a button the air releases and it fits into a tiny carrying pouch.

